property.value: Although great care has been put into creating this logical data model and supporting documents, no guarantee can be given with regards to the technical correctness of the content

OView.comment: As regards Collateral received instrument the following topics need to be discussed: * identification of Credit default swaps (CDS) which are considered a Financial guarantee * relationship with Protection arragement * assignment of protection related attributes

It needs to be evaluated if the approach for Instrument role should be moved to a lower level in the Instrument hierarchy, e.g. Financial asset loan (excluding repurchase agreement), Financial asset reverse repurchase agreement, Off-balance sheet item given financial guarantee instrument. Moving the functionality to a lower level in the hierarchy would allow to incorporate additional business rules / logic into the LDM, e.g. which Instrument types (by product) may actually be Financial assets, Financial liabilities, Collateral received, Collateral given, Off-balance sheet item given, Off-balance sheet item received?
Treatment of baskets of securities and indices needs to be described, i.e. is not covered.
Double click to edit the text.

This information should be organised in a similar fashion as for Instruments, see subtypes of Financial asset instrument. However, it needs to be taken into account that Credit facilities represent Off-balance sheet items (given / received) only.
Moving LEI to Party code Institutional sector should be assigned to subtypes with allowed values per subtype, e.g. Central bank.Institutional sector is restricted to Central banks (S121)
How do we distinguish between asset and liability Exchange tradable derivative positions?
Similar approach as for Instruments should be applied for interest rate related information of credit facilities.
Synthetic securitisations involving an SSPE have not been modeled so far.
Are there use cases for Repurchase agreements where Equity or Fund securities are involved?

The current design of Security collateral implies that, in case different Securities are provided as Collateral, each one of them has to be registered as a Security collateral. Would it make sense to review this design? Does it reflect reality? Wouldn't it make sense to be able to register multiple Securities as a Security collateral?
Early redemptions included indicator and Accrued interests for market values indicator are not Security-by-Security but for the whole report. They cannot be derived.
Credit transfer other than Securitisation and Covered bond program has not been modeled so far.

Detailed analysis of Security against a fee borrowing and lending transaction regarding the representation of the fee - currently as Securities borrowing and lending transaction cash as collateral component - is required.
The relationship to a Swap contract has to be discussed.
